text: In many varieties of informal English, including AAVE and some Southern U.S. dialects, phrases like somethin awful can be placed at the end of a sentence or clause to serve as an intensifier. Instead of saying Hes been wheezing and coughing a lot or very badly, the speaker says He been wheezin and coughin somethin awful, which emphasizes the severity of the action. The phrase somethin awful here modifies how badly he is wheezing and coughing.  This construction isnt unique to AAVE, but it is commonly found in informal, colloquial speech.
